stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    state "Quotes Acceptance Flow" {
        [*] --> QuoteDraft

        QuoteDraft --> PendingInternalApproval : Sales Creates & Submits
        PendingInternalApproval --> SentToCustomer : Internal Approval Granted (e.g., Manager, Finance)
        PendingInternalApproval --> QuoteDraft : Internal Approval Rejected (Sales Revises)

        SentToCustomer --> CustomerReviewing : Customer Receives & Views
        CustomerReviewing --> Accepted : Customer Approves Quote
        CustomerReviewing --> CustomerRequestedRevisions : Customer Requests Changes
        CustomerReviewing --> Rejected : Customer Declines Quote
        CustomerReviewing --> Expired : Quote Validity Period Ends

        CustomerRequestedRevisions --> QuoteRevised : Sales Revises Quote
        QuoteRevised --> SentToCustomer : Sales Sends Revised Quote

        Accepted --> AcceptedProcess
        Rejected --> RejectedExpiredProcess
        Expired --> RejectedExpiredProcess

        state "Accepted Quote Post-Processing" as AcceptedProcess {
            OrderCreated
            CRM_QuoteStatusUpdate_Won
            CRM_OpportunityStatusUpdate_Won
            System_Notifications_Won
        }
        state "Rejected/Expired Quote Post-Processing" as RejectedExpiredProcess {
            CRM_QuoteStatusUpdate_Lost
            CRM_OpportunityStatusUpdate_Lost
            System_Notifications_Lost
            ArchiveQuote
        }

        OrderCreated --> [*] : Process Completed (Won)
        System_Notifications_Won --> [*] : Final State (Won)
        System_Notifications_Lost --> [*] : Final State (Lost)
    }

    note for QuoteDraft
        Sales team creates the initial quote record.
        CRM: Quote record status 'Draft'.
        Actions: Populate product details, pricing, terms.
    end note

    note for PendingInternalApproval
        Quote awaits internal approval (e.g., Sales Manager, Finance Dept.) before sending.
        CRM: Quote status 'Pending Internal Approval'.
        System: Approval workflow initiated, notifications to approvers.
    end note

    note for SentToCustomer
        Quote is formally dispatched to the customer (e.g., via email, customer portal).
        CRM: Quote status 'Sent'.
        System: Customer portal link generated, email notification sent, validity period starts.
    end note

    note for CustomerReviewing
        Customer is actively reviewing the quote details.
        CRM: Quote status 'In Review'.
        System: Tracking of customer views (if portal used), potential for customer comments.
    end note

    note for CustomerRequestedRevisions
        Customer requests modifications to the quote details, terms, or pricing.
        CRM: Quote status 'Revision Requested'.
        System: Notification to Sales team, potential for internal comments/tasks.
    end note

    note for QuoteRevised
        Sales team updates the quote based on customer feedback and re-validates internally.
        CRM: New version created or existing updated, status 'Revised'.
        Actions: Adjust items, discounts, terms; potentially re-initiate internal approval.
    end note

    note for Accepted
        Customer formally accepts the quote without further changes.
        CRM: Quote status 'Accepted'.
        Triggers downstream processes for order fulfillment.
    end note

    note for Rejected
        Customer formally declines the quote.
        CRM: Quote status 'Declined'.
        Actions: Capture reason for decline.
    end note

    note for Expired
        Quote validity period ends without customer decision or acceptance.
        CRM: Quote status 'Expired'.
        System: Automated expiry notification, opportunity might be considered lost.
    end note

    note for OrderCreated
        Upon acceptance, a new order, contract, or project is initiated and created.
        CRM: New Order/Contract record created, linked to the accepted Quote and Opportunity.
        ERP/Billing: Integration point for creating sales orders or invoices.
    end note

    note for OpportunityLost
        Associated sales opportunity is marked as 'Closed Lost'.
        CRM: Opportunity status 'Closed Lost'.
        Actions: Analyze loss reasons, update sales forecasts.
    end note

    note for CRM_QuoteStatusUpdate_Won
        CRM: Quote record status updated to 'Closed Won'.
    end note

    note for CRM_OpportunityStatusUpdate_Won
        CRM: Associated Opportunity status updated to 'Closed Won'.
        Actions: Update sales pipeline metrics.
    end note

    note for System_Notifications_Won
        Internal stakeholders (e.g., Sales, Operations, Finance) notified of acceptance.
        System: Automated email alerts, task creation for follow-up actions.
    end note

    note for CRM_QuoteStatusUpdate_Lost
        CRM: Quote record status updated to 'Closed Lost' or 'Expired'.
    end note

    note for CRM_OpportunityStatusUpdate_Lost
        CRM: Associated Opportunity status updated to 'Closed Lost'.
        Actions: Update sales pipeline metrics, record loss reason.
    end note

    note for System_Notifications_Lost
        Internal stakeholders (e.g., Sales Manager) notified of decline/expiry.
        System: Automated email alerts.
    end note

    note for ArchiveQuote
        Quote record moved to an archive status or flagged for retention based on company policy.
        CRM: Status updated to 'Archived'.
    end note